name: Sunsets in the Yarra Valley V2

metadata.name: The Lonely Tree
metadata.description: This is one of my favourite photos I've taken. It captures the moment I was running to the top of that hill to get a shot of the sunset looking out to the views. I paused and looked up to see this tree lit perfectly with the orange-yellow hues of the quickly-disappearing sun. I snapped this photo mindful of the small window to see these shades from above the hill, not thinking anything of it. As it turns out, the rush I felt while taking that shot is now immortalised in the photo itself (and now on the blockchain too!). Every time I look at it, that same feeling is invoked.
